javaslang

Interface Algebra.HigherKinded<A,TYPE extends Algebra.HigherKinded<?,TYPE>>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - Component type of the type to be constructed.
    TYPE - Container type of the type to be constructed.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Algebra.Monad<A,M>, List<T>, Option<T>, Seq<T>, Stream<T>, Traversable<T>, Try<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    List.AbstractList, List.Cons, List.Nil, Option.None, Option.Some, Stream.AbstractStream, Stream.Cons, Stream.Deferred, Stream.Nil, Try.Failure, Try.Success
    Enclosing class:
    Algebra

    public static interface Algebra.HigherKinded<A,TYPE extends Algebra.HigherKinded<?,TYPE>>

    A type HigherKinded declares a generic type constructor, which consists of an inner type (component type) and an outer type (container type).

    HigherKinded is needed to (partially) simulate Higher-Kinded/Higher-Order Types, which are not part of the Java language but needed for generic type constructors.

    Example: Algebra.Monad.flatMap(java.util.function.Function)
